keyFacts: The document is a confidential law enforcement travel record listing 30 international flights for an individual from 2004 to 2019.
Travel patterns show frequent transatlantic flights between Los Angeles (LAX) and London (LHR), with additional trips to/from Miami, Nassau, Vancouver, Manila, and New York.
The record includes a flight from Miami to Nassau, Bahamas in May 2009, a location associated with Jeffrey Epstein's private island.
The document is marked 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive' and 'CONFIDENTIAL', indicating its use in an investigation.
The subject's name and personal details are redacted in this excerpt, showing only travel data.
